cs.NI, cs.SI, cs.GT, cs.IT, cs.MM

Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper proposes a solution to better utilize the limited resources of base-stations in wireless networks by enabling local common-interests sharing through D2D communications. 
2. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) - The paper focuses on motivating physically neighboring users to form a social group to share common interests. 
3. cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) - The paper proposes an incentive mechanism to motivate social grouping among selfish users. 
4. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper analyzes the optimal equal-reciprocal scheme that maximizes local sharing content while ensuring fairness among users. 
5. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper considers a group of smartphone users interested in the same network content, which may involve multimedia content.
